==English==
===Etymology===
{{F.}} [[synchicité]]
===Noun===
'''synchicity'''
#(''multimedia'') specialist qualitative term in [[multimedia]] to denote the degree of [[synchronization]] between media elements, ''e.g. audio and video, audio and subtitles, animation, vector graphics, etc''.  This is an essential feature of the [[World_Wide_Web_Consortium|World Wide Web Consortium]] time-based multimedia standards :[[SMIL]] (Synchronized Multimedia Integration Language), [[SVG]] (Scalable Vector Graphics) and [[Timed Text]].

